{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01HznhTpdGuKRxjorP8zCRJJ","type":"tool_result","content":"{\"body\":\"## Description\\n\\nThe Odin's Throne monitor service at https://monitor.fenrirledger.com/ is not deployed. The service exists in the codebase (`development/monitor/`) but has not been deployed to GKE Autopilot yet.\\n\\n## Expected Behavior\\n\\nhttps://monitor.fenrirledger.com/ should serve the Odin's Throne monitor UI, providing live agent log streaming and report generation.\\n\\n## Affected Code\\n\\n- `development/monitor/` â€” Monitor service (Hono backend)\\n- `development/monitor-ui/` â€” Monitor UI\\n- `infrastructure/k8s/` â€” K8s manifests (needs new deployment, service, ingress)\\n- `.github/workflows/deploy.yml` â€” Needs deploy-monitor job\\n\\n## Acceptance Criteria\\n\\n- [ ] Monitor service deployed to GKE with Helm or K8s manifests\\n- [ ] DNS record for monitor.fenrirledger.com pointing to GKE ingress\\n- [ ] Managed TLS certificate provisioned\\n- [ ] https://monitor.fenrirledger.com/ loads the monitor UI\\n- [ ] Deploy workflow includes monitor service build+push+deploy\\n\\n## Notes\\n\\n- Related issues: #885 (log streaming), #910 (web worker), #911 (local dev), #917 (WebSocket)\\n- The monitor service was recently migrated from odin http-server (PR #935)\\n- Auth should use oauth2-proxy sidecar pattern (same as Umami â€” PR #934, #933)\\n\\n---\\nGenerated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\",\"comments\":[{\"id\":\"IC_kwDORWS4Us7yH5Z0\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"declanshanaghy\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"OWNER\",\"body\":\"## FiremanDecko â†’ Loki Handoff\\n\\n**Branch:** feat/issue-945-deploy-monitor | **PR:** https://github.com/declanshanaghy/fenrir-ledger/pull/948\\n\\n### What changed\\n\\nThe Helm chart scaffold, DNS record, static IP, Docker images, build/push jobs, and deploy job were already in place. This PR completes the missing oauth2-proxy protection layer:\\n\\n1. **`infrastructure/helm/odin-throne/templates/deployment-ui.yaml`** â€” Added oauth2-proxy sidecar to the UI pod (same pattern as Umami). Fronts nginx on port 80, listens on port 4180. Mounts `emails.txt` from `odin-throne-oauth2-proxy-secrets` for allowlist auth. Sidecar is gated by `oauth2Proxy.enabled`.\\n\\n2. **`infrastructure/helm/odin-throne/templates/service-ui.yaml`** â€” Added `cloud.google.com/backend-config` and `cloud.google.com/neg` annotations. When oauth2-proxy is enabled, `targetPort` points to `oauth2-proxy` (4180) instead of nginx (80).\\n\\n3. **`infrastructure/helm/odin-throne/values.yaml` / `values-prod.yaml`** â€” Added `oauth2Proxy` block with image, port 4180, redirect URL, and resources.\\n\\n4. **`.github/workflows/deploy.yml`** â€” Added `Create/update Odin's Throne oauth2-proxy secrets` step to `deploy-odin-throne` job. Uses `kubectl create secret --dry-run=client | apply` (idempotent). Requires new GitHub secrets: `MONITOR_OAUTH2_PROXY_COOKIE_SECRET`, `ODINS_THRONE_CLIENT_ID`, `ODINS_THRONE_CLIENT_SECRET`.\\n\\n### How to verify\\n\\n1. `helm template ./infrastructure/helm/odin-throne -f infrastructure/helm/odin-throne/values-prod.yaml` â€” should render without errors\\n2. Check that `odin-throne-ui` Service spec has `targetPort: oauth2-proxy`\\n3. Merge PR, trigger deploy, visit `https://monitor.fenrirledger.com/` â€” should redirect to Google OAuth consent screen\\n4. After auth, monitor UI should load and WebSocket stream should work\\n\\n### Required GitHub Secrets (must be added before deploy)\\n\\n- `ODINS_THRONE_CLIENT_ID` â€” Google OAuth client ID for monitor (can reuse or create new OAuth app)\\n- `ODINS_THRONE_CLIENT_SECRET` â€” Google OAuth client secret\\n- `MONITOR_OAUTH2_PROXY_COOKIE_SECRET` â€” 32-byte cookie secret, generate with: `openssl rand -hex 16`\\n\\n### Edge cases for Loki to test\\n\\n- oauth2-proxy health check at `/ping` (port 4180) â€” BackendConfig expects this path/port\\n- WebSocket upgrades through nginx proxy after oauth2-proxy auth: the `Authorization` header must pass through correctly\\n- If `MONITOR_OAUTH2_PROXY_COOKIE_SECRET` is not added to GitHub secrets, deploy step will fail with an empty secret value\\n- Cert provisioning for `monitor.fenrirledger.com` may take 10-20 min after first deploy\\n\\n**Build:** tsc PASS + next build PASS (37 routes). Ready for QA.\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-03-15T04:06:05Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"isMinimized\":false,\"minimizedReason\":\"\",\"reactionGroups\":[],\"url\":\"https://github.com/declanshanaghy/fenrir-ledger/issues/945#issuecomment-4062156404\",\"viewerDidAuthor\":true},{\"id\":\"IC_kwDORWS4Us7yH_70\",\"author\":{\"login\":\"declanshanaghy\"},\"authorAssociation\":\"OWNER\",\"body\":\"## QA Verdict: PASS\\n\\n**Loki (QA Tester) â€” 2026-03-15**\\n**Branch:** `feat/issue-945-deploy-monitor`\\n**PR:** #948\\n\\n---\\n\\n### New Tests: 0\\n\\nInfrastructure-only change. No testable application code was modified.\\n\\nAll 5 changed files are outside the automated test boundary per QA rules (Helm charts, deploy workflows, and YAML config files are explicitly banned from automated testing):\\n\\n| File | Type |\\n|------|------|\\n| `.github/workflows/deploy.yml` | CI/CD deploy workflow |\\n| `infrastructure/helm/odin-throne/templates/deployment-ui.yaml` | Helm template |\\n| `infrastructure/helm/odin-throne/templates/service-ui.yaml` | Helm template |\\n| `infrastructure/helm/odin-throne/values-prod.yaml` | Helm values |\\n| `infrastructure/helm/odin-throne/values.yaml` | Helm values |\\n\\nZero TypeScript, zero React components, zero API routes, zero hooks, zero utilities changed. Vitest has nothing to cover here.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Verification Results\\n\\n| Check | Result |\\n|-------|--------|\\n| Vitest (59 files, 771 tests) | PASS â€” 0 failures |\\n| tsc --noEmit | PASS â€” 0 errors |\\n| Working tree | Clean |\\n| quality/reports/ | Clean |\\n| Branch vs main | Up to date |\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Issues Found\\n\\nNone.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Tests Passed (Existing Suite)\\n\\n- All 771 existing Vitest unit and integration tests pass without regression\\n- This infrastructure change introduces no risk to application code\\n\\n---\\n\\nInfrastructure-only change â€” Vitest verification only, no new tests needed.\",\"createdAt\":\"2026-03-15T04:23:26Z\",\"includesCreatedEdit\":false,\"isMinimized\":false,\"minimizedReason\":\"\",\"reactionGroups\":[],\"url\":\"https://github.com/declanshanaghy/fenrir-ledger/issues/945#issuecomment-4062183156\",\"viewerDidAuthor\":true}],\"title\":\"Deploy Odin's Throne monitor service to GKE\"}","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5c6dc13c-5cd7-4e6a-a270-c59c976993b2","uuid":"a3b4554f-e61d-44d1-84cf-3eaa7f458842","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"{\"body\":\"## Description\\n\\nThe Odin's Throne monitor service at https://monitor.fenrirledger.com/ is not deployed. The service exists in the codebase (`development/monitor/`) but has not been deployed to GKE Autopilot yet.\\n\\n## Expected Behavior\\n\\nhttps://monitor.fenrirledger.com/ should serve the Odin's Throne monitor UI, providing live agent log streaming and report generation.\\n\\n## Affected Code\\n\\n- `development/monitor/` â€” Monitor service (Hono backend)\\n- `development/monitor-ui/` â€” Monitor UI\\n- `infrastructure/k8s/` â€” K8s manifests (needs new deployment, service, ingress)\\n- `.github/workflows/deploy.yml` â€” Needs deploy-monitor job\\n\\n## Acceptance Criteria\\n\\n- [ ] Monitor service deployed to GKE with Helm or K8s manifests\\n- [ ] DNS record for monitor.fenrirledger.com pointing to GKE ingress\\n- [ ] Managed TLS certificate provisioned\\n- [ ] https://monitor.fenrirledger.com/ loads the monitor UI\\n- [ ] Deploy workflow includes monitor service build+push+deploy\\n\\n## Notes\\n\\n- Related issues: #885 (log streaming), #910 (web worker), #911 (local dev), #917 (WebSocket)\\n- The monitor service was recently migrated from odin http-server (PR #935)\\n-